channel.title: Cannot find symbol
channel.description:
Well im using a figment source, and i decided to clear the client.java up by handling majority of the crap thats in there.
I decided to make a handler called ObjectSpawn.java
Now when i add these [code] ObjectSpawn = new ObjectSpawn(); public static ObjectSpawn ObjectSpawn = null; [/code]
Into the server.java I get these errors (And yes there in the correct Place) [code] server.java:139: cannot find symbol symbol : class ObjectSpawn location: class server public static ObjectSpawn ObjectSpawn = null; ^ server.java:40: cannot find symbol symbol : class ObjectSpawn location: class server ObjectSpawn = new ObjectSpawn(); ^ Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 2 errors Finished! Press any key to continue . . . [/code]
My class name is ObjectSpawn.java and i dont see why im getting error's Can someone push me in the right direction please? :p

item.title: Cannot find symbol
item.dc:creator: @I_PK_Pigeons I PK Pigeons

[quote=“si force, post:3, topic:253358”][quote author=warlock 999 link=topic=334703.msg2605442#msg2605442 date=1230494640]
Delete each one of them errors, like public static ObjectSpawn ObjectSpawn = null;
[/quote]

He’s trying to add them, Not delete them.

@I PK PIGEONS;

Although it should work, Try putting the second ObjectSpawn as a lowercase in the part;

public static ObjectSpawn objectspawn = null;

Not fully sure, But try, I doubt it’s the cause though.[/quote]

I tried it and its not the cause, it gave me another 4 errors
